review_blob:
bottle 37.5cl @STOOM brewpub, tht 12/17
Appearance is maple syrup/sherry-ish. No head, no lacing, no carbo. Syrup!
Aroma has pickles, some cloves, vinegar, appelstroop, cat food, persian carpet. Nice complexity, weird balance, still enjoyable. Dont ask me why. Loads of sherry/applewine hints.
Taste is more apples, sherry, cherries. Some raisins, some cola-herbalness, old cheese, barn, cellar.
Mouthfeel is really thick and syrup with a soft sour finish. Vinegary port stuff. Pretty sweet. Loads of cheesy funk.
beer_name: Hof Ten Dormaal Taste Lab - B-Wine

review_blob:
bottle 33cl @STOOM brewpub, private collection. bottledate 11/11/15, tht 11/11/17
Appearance is golden/orange, light shine/haze. Small white head, some soapy lacing.
Aroma has honey, summery flowers, hops, some marmalade/orange.
Taste has more citrus, orange. Some caramel and yeasty notes. Bit weird dusty feeling/taste.
Finish is smooth, soft bitter. Bit watery texture. More marmalade follows.
Feels almost like a toned down mooie nel. Pity.

draught, 20cl @STOOM brewpub. Unsure which batch (2nd from 7000L foudre?)
Appearance is murky orange/red/brown. Hazy. Small dimishing offwhite head.
Aroma has loads of red fruit, nice stable funk, floral, some vanilla, pepper, cherries! wow.
Taste is more red fruit, cherries, grapes, some perfume/floral notes. some apple. Yeasty/bubblegum too.
Finishes really smooth, soft, mild sour. Silk texture, more red fruit, some lactic acid pushing now. Solid stuff.
beer_name: Oersoep Wild at Heart (God is Goed)

review_blob:
bottle 33cl @STOOM brewpub; bottled 05/15.
Appearance is clear reddish brown. Really light for a porter imo. White/beige thin head. Loads of carbonation.
Aroma has lots of smoke/meat, some caramel/malty notes. Blueberries (yay!), and some metal.. cardboard.. yeast. Old geezer..
Taste has more smoke, malt, berries. Bit one-sided. Reminds me a lot of a Schlenkerla Mrzen now.. (which is good..?)
Medium bodied, malty bitter finish. Damn. Hou op, schei uit.

bottle 50cl @STOOM brewpub. bottled 04/15, tht 04/16
Appearance is dark brown with a red/black hue. Coffee/coke/dr pepper-ish. Small beige head with some soapy lacing.
Aroma has toast, brown malts, honey, some coffee/grass/floral and spicy notes.
Taste is mostly roast/toast, dark bread with lots of espresso. Some caramel middle notes.
Palate is dry/bitter, focusing on burnt/coffee/roast with some toffee and caramel. Nice beer.
The soundtrack for this beer was Descendents - Coffee Mug (Everything Sucks). Solid.
beer_name: Weird Beard Upside To A Down Day

review_blob:
bottle 25cl @STOOM brewpub; tht 02/11/2017.
Appearance is clear, blond white wine-ish. Soft small white head with some lacing. Looks clean!
Aroma has grass/hops, some sweetness, honey/malt, oats, spicyness, coriander/spices? yeast, bread, lemon. bit floral/pepper.
Taste is grainy, citrus/lemon, yeasty. Getting some nice fresh spicyness.
Palate has a soft bitter creamy finish. Ends pretty bitter for its dryness. More lemon and pepper in the aftertaste.

Geen hoge verwachtingen. Kleine brouwer die al een tijdje meedraait. Precies zoals Klein Duimpje ofzo. Zit de laatste tijd wat meer tap-take-overs en collabs met rooie dop en kompaan (die coole dudes) te doen dus ik dacht, hee wat gebeurt er.

Redelijk nieuwe variant, voor hen. Gekke hoppen dus, want hip. (Ze maken het trouwens bij Jopen).

Maargoed, de vorige/laatste 3 uiltjes waren meh, weer meh, laat maar.

Deze daarentegen. Je ruikt GRAS. Superdik, broeiig, harsig gras. De smaak is supervol, alsof je mond vol met hopcones zit, zonder daadwerkelijk stuk te gaan op de bitterheid. Beetje zoet, niet zo gistig, beetje harsh/ruw op de keel opt eind. Maar goeie shit jongens. Ik had op een gegeven moment echt citroen. En wat tropisch fruit. Van die passievruchtige/watermeloenen meuk.

Bottle, 33cl. Online. Aroma: Roasted malts, coffee, toast and wood. Appearance: Black with a brown head. Good head with no lacing left. Head disappears quite quickly too. Taste: Sour, caramel, coffee. Palate: Thick (almost creamy). Definitely has the lactose/milky sourness. Good stuff. Easy-going. New session beer!

Bottle, 35.5cl, FlinkGegist. Aroma: Plums, caramel, bit of red fruit, roasted malts. Appearance: Lovely ruby red/dark chestnut brown. Wonderful cream coloured small head with medium to minimal lacing. Taste: Licorice, herbal, plums, vanilla. Palate: Busty amount of carbonation. Interesting feel and palate. Some licorice and candy alongside the hoppy, bittery ending.
beer_name: Flying Dog Horn Dog Barley Wine

review_blob: Bottle, 30cl. Online. Aroma: Very nice roasted malts. Some coffee and chocolate. Appearance: Good head with sticky lacings. Really black beer. Taste: Roasted, almost burnt malts. Bit of coffee, hint of chocolate. Alcohol, caramel, banana. Palate: Medium/thick body. Id like it thicker from the rye. Good carbonation.

Bottle, 30cl, Mitra Nijmegen. Aroma: Caramel, roasted malts, alcohol, plastic. Appearance: Hazy hazelnutbrown with a very light-brown head. Taste: Toasted bread, alcohol, caramel, some plastic as well. Palate: Medium/thick with some easy-going carbonation. Dry with a little bitteryness at the end.

Bottle, 30cl. Albert Heijn XL Nijmegen. Aroma: Grass, herbal, citrus, honey, coriander. Appearance: Honey/yellow/orange colour with a slightly offwhite head. Taste: Malty with some citrus and something sweet. Honey. Palate: Sweet, honey aftertaste with some herbal bitterness from the hops and coriander lingering. A very good witbier.

Bottle, 30cl, Mitra Nijmegen. Aroma: Caramel, malt, banana, grass, honey. Appearance: Hazelnut-brown colour with a very thin, quick disappearing head. Taste: Sweet. Caramel, bit of banana. Metallic too. Palate: Light/medium body with a bit of carbonation. Sweet lingers in the aftertaste.
beer_name: De Leckere Special Edition Dunkel Weizen

review_blob: Bottle, 33cl, Mitra Nijmegen. Aroma: Malts, citrus, grass. Appearance: Cloudy yellow/orange. Minimal lacing and foam. Taste: Wheat, citrus. Palate: Medium/light. Creamy and a bit soapy but fresh and bittery aftertaste.

Bottle, 50cl, Mitra Nijmegen. Aroma: Caramel. Appearance: Ruby red colour with an amber head. Small dotted lacing. Taste: Caramel, wheat. Palate: Medium/thick body with not too much carbonation. BIttery aftertaste.

Bottle, 35.5cl, Online. Aroma: Coffee, chocolate, red peppers, whiff of alcohol. Appearance: Very, very dark brown/black. Dark brown head with minimal lacing. Head disappears fast. Taste: Roasted malts, roasted coffee, lots of chocolate. Palate: Tip of the tongue carbonation from the coffee. Chocolate lasts and lasts. Medium/thick body. Dry finish.

Bottle, 33cl, Online. Aroma: Roasted malts, coffee, floral notes (hops!). Appearance: Thick black with a solid brown head. Lovely lacing. Taste: Very nice. Caramel, coffee, roasted malts. Palate: Thick body, wonderful. Smoke/peated malts carry the taste down to a nice dry/bittery finish.
A very good porter.

Bottle, 33cl, Online. Aroma: Leather, smoke, whisky and some hops on the background. Appearance: Black as night. Brown head. Small dotty lacings linger. Taste: This stuff is godly. Dark as an IRS, floral as an IPA. Roasted malts, whisky, herbal, leather, hops. Everything a man or woman could want. Just missed a tad depth. Palate: Hoppyness everywhere. Smooth whisky notes carry the hops down. Pretty thick with some spicy carbonation. Heavy hitter Id say.
I could drink this ambrosia for days.

Bottle, 33cl, online. Aroma: Alcohol, almost nothing else. Appearance: Dark brown with light brown head. Lots of lacing. Taste: Licorice, bread, cardboard. Bit roasty, bit bitter. Palate: Dry, licorice lingering. Thick, but not as thick as Id like it to be.

Bottle, 33cl. Online. Aroma: Roasted, herbal, coffee, smoke, teensy bit sour. Appearance: Full black colour. Minimal head and lacing. Taste: Roasted malts, coffee, blue cheese. Not sour in the taste at all. Palate: Almost no carbonation. Pretty bitter and thin.

Bottle, 33cl. Online. Aroma: Lactose, smoke, roasted malts, coffee with a bit of hops. Appearance: Black. Brownish head. Taste: Coffee, roasted malts, no chocolate to be tasted really. Palate: Thick and smooth. Hops last a while. Fizzy coffee-carbonation.

Bottle, 33cl, friend. Aroma: Cherries, red fruit, roasted malts. Appearance: Dark brown/black. Still see-through. Brown-ish head. Good stuff. Taste: Plums, fresh bread, roast, coffee. The bread was very nice. Palate: Roasty lingering with a nice bitter.
Wonderful stuff.
Bottle, 33cl, Online. Aroma: Wood, caramel, candy. Appearance: Amber/golden colour, not a lot of lacing. Taste: Wonderful, wood, sweetness. Malty caramel. Palate: Caramel lingers on.
Bottle, 33cl, Friend. Aroma: Malt, citrus, hops, yeasty. Appearance: Yellow/amber with a good yellow-ish, white head. Taste: Citrus, hops, fruits. Palate. Smooth. Lingering hoppyness.

Bottle, 33cl, Online. Aroma: Caramel, pine, sweet. Appearance: Off-white, yellow head. Dark, chestnut coloured. Nice lacing. Taste: Salty, hoppy, caramel, nuts. Palate: Alcohol and sweet. Nutty in the end.

Bottle, 33cl, Supermarket (AHXL) . Aroma: Malt, caramel, alcohol. Appearance: Dark chestnut brown. Small head with a teeny bit of lacing left. Taste: Caramel, malts, wood, nuts, alcohol. Palate: Fairly light body, short-lived almond aftertaste. Turns quite dry afterwards.

Bottle, 50cl, Supermarket (AHXL) . Aroma: Wheat and citrus. Appearance: Hazy/cloudy honeyed yellow colour. Nice white foam with small lacing. Taste: Banana, honey, citrus. Palate: Goes down smooth. A bit medium/thick body. What youd want from a weizen. Malty sweetness with mild bitterness is medium/longlasting.
Very nice weizen.

Bottle, 33cl, Online. Aroma: Salt, chocolate, licorice. Appearance: Pitch black with a small brown head. Disappears immediately leaving some lacing. Taste: Licorice, dark chocolate, coffee, vanilla. Palate: Full bodied, milky. Nice! Thick/creamy coffee/chocolate lingering. Smooth.
Good Imperial Porter. Would recommend.

Bottle, 33cl, Online. Aroma: Herbal, (red) pepper, flowers, something sweet (heather, honey) Appearance: Nice golden/amber. Good, small head. Taste: Wood, herbal, honey, alcohol. Palate: Immediate red pepper carbonation/fizz on the tongue, followed by a nice lasting honey sweetness.
beer_name: Heather Ales Alba Scots Pine Ale

review_blob: Bottle, 33cl, Online. Aroma: Malts, Smoke.  Appearance: So much foam, it guzzled over. Very dark chestnut brown colour. Taste: Smoked malts, sweet, wood, nuts.  Palate: Lasting sweetness.

Bottle, 33cl, Online.
Aroma: Roasted malts, coffee, nuts, herbal, barn/hay. Appearance: Black with a very big off-white head. Taste: Black pepper, roasted malts, nuts, citrus. Palate: Lots and lots of carbonation on the tongue, light body with a coffee, hoppy aftertaste.
Interesting mix of a saison with a porter.
beer_name: xxx St-Feuillien & Green Flash / Black Saison

review_blob:
Bottle, 33cl, Online. Aroma: Tropical fruits, American hops, malts and some sweetness. Appearance: Orange amber with a nice lingering head. Taste: Orange, tropical fruits, sweet, hint of candy. Palate: Medium body with a long, dry, bittery, hoppy finish.
Very lovely Pale Ale.

Bottle, 33cl, Online. 
Aroma: Roasted malts, chocolate, red fruits, vanilla. Appearance: Black with beige creamy head. Taste: Roasted malts, caramel, toffee. Palate: Thick. Nice bittery aftertaste that turns dry.
A deep stout!

Bottle, 33cl, Online.
Aroma: Floral, grassy, some heather, honey  Appearance: Pours golden brown. Off-white foam with nice lacing. Taste: Sweet, floral, malts. Palate: light to medium body, not much carbonation. Dry.
Nice ale, love the floral/honey combination and taste!

Bottle, 33cl, FlinkGegist (Delft)
Aroma: Coffee, a bit musty, put me off a bit. Appearance: Pours dark, little to no foam, no lacing. Taste: Sweet, coffee, hint of chocolate. Coffee-bitter in the end. Palate: light to medium body, fizzly carbonation on the tongue.

Bottle, 33cl, online.
Aroma: very, very malty, hint of citrus; really nice! Appeareance: Chestnut and cloudy. Nice head! Taste: very, very malty. Reminds me of mashing on brewday. Sweetish. Palate: thick body, pleasant carbonation. Sweetness lasts.

Bottle, 33cl, online.
Dark, nut brown, cloudy colour. Smell is a bit malty, plastic. Taste is very alcoholish with a nice long bittery aftertaste.
